{
  "stem": "17761.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they deported place by place into that Transnistria, including the Jews who remained somehow alive in somehow in Bessarabia and northern Bukovina.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Tschernowitz had to come the last.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then they started in Moldova with Dorohoi, D-O-R-O-H-O-I, and some little places around Dorohoi, like [INAUDIBLE], [INAUDIBLE], [INAUDIBLE], and they also were deported into Transnistria.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But then something happened and we do not know exactly what.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Some claim that he got some warning from the United States of America, this Antonescu, that he would have to-- to pay for what he was doing and the deportation stopped.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So only a part of Tschernowitz has been deported.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the other part, those who succeeded to remain, they remained in Tschernowitz and [NON-ENGLISH], which is the place of my wife, was not anymore-- which is close next to Dorohoi, was not deported anymore.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And from this point, no other Jews were deported from Romania into Transnistria.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So this explains you a little bit the picture of how this worked.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were in Vatra-Dornei.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A day before Hoshana Rabbah, we were all advised that we have to prepare our things.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We have to leave.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We will be all evacuated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was the term.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Romanian authorities.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was also published by the drummer of the city.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a drummer who used to-- still we-- I see this drummer.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he announced this to everybody, that we have to hand over to the-- to the city hall all our foreign currency we have, all silver, all gold, those precious metals, and if not, it is by death punishment, and that we have to be 24 hours later at the big station-- there were two train stations in that place-- at the big station for to leave the place.",
      "word_count": 69
    }
  ],
